# Hoon Workbook

The Workbook is the place to sharpen your Hoon skills. Each entry in the
Workbook is a code walkthrough followed by exercises.

- The [Caesar Cipher](/docs/learn/arvo/workbook/caesar) shows you how to build a simple method of message obfuscation.

- The [Recursion](/docs/learn/arvo/workbook/recursion) walkthrough will explain common patterns of recursion in programming and how to implement them in Hoon.

- The [Digits](/docs/learn/arvo/workbook/digits) example demonstrates how to decompose a number into a list of its digits.

- The [Magic 8-Ball](/docs/learn/arvo/workbook/eightball) example emulates everyone's favorite decision-making machine.

- The [Traffic-light](/docs/learn/arvo/workbook/traffic-light) example demonstrates how to creates a state machine in Hoon.

- The [Bomb-defusing](/docs/learn/arvo/workbook/bomb) exercise shows how to program, well, a bomb-defusing scenario.
